21#include <stdio.h>
22#include "mpc-impl.h"
23
24/* Special case op = 1 + i*y for tiny y (see algorithms.tex).
25 Return 0 if special formula fails, otherwise put in z1 the approximate
26 value which needs to be converted to rop.
27 z1 is a temporary variable with enough precision.
28 */
29static int
30mpc_asin_special (mpc_ptr rop, mpc_srcptr op, mpc_rnd_t rnd, mpc_ptr z1)
31{
32 mpfr_exp_t ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref (op));
33 mpfr_t abs_y;
34 mpfr_prec_t p;
35 int inex;
36
37 /* |Re(asin(1+i*y)) - pi/2| <= y^(1/2) */
38 if (ey >= 0 || ((-ey) / 2 < mpfr_get_prec (mpc_realref (z1))))
39 return 0;
40
41 mpfr_const_pi (mpc_realref (z1), MPFR_RNDN);
42 mpfr_div_2exp (mpc_realref (z1), mpc_realref (z1), 1, MPFR_RNDN); /* exact */
43 p = mpfr_get_prec (mpc_realref (z1));
44 /* if z1 has precision p, the error on z1 is 1/2*ulp(z1) = 2^(-p) so far,
45 and since ey <= -2p, then y^(1/2) <= 1/2*ulp(z1) too, thus the total
46 error is bounded by ulp(z1) */
47 if (!mpfr_can_round (mpc_realref(z1), p, MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
48 mpfr_get_prec (mpc_realref(rop)) +
49 (MPC_RND_RE(rnd) == MPFR_RNDN)))
50 return 0;
51
52 /* |Im(asin(1+i*y)) - y^(1/2)| <= (1/12) * y^(3/2) for y >= 0 (err >= 0)
53 |Im(asin(1-i*y)) + y^(1/2)| <= (1/12) * y^(3/2) for y >= 0 (err <= 0) */
54 abs_y[0] = mpc_imagref (op)[0];
55 if (mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op)))
56 MPFR_CHANGE_SIGN (abs_y);
57 inex = mpfr_sqrt (mpc_imagref (z1), abs_y, MPFR_RNDN); /* error <= 1/2 ulp */
58 if (mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op)))
59 MPFR_CHANGE_SIGN (mpc_imagref (z1));
60 /* If z1 has precision p, the error on z1 is 1/2*ulp(z1) = 2^(-p) so far,
61 and (1/12) * y^(3/2) <= (1/8) * y * y^(1/2) <= 2^(ey-3)*2^p*ulp(y^(1/2))
62 thus for p+ey-3 <= -1 we have (1/12) * y^(3/2) <= (1/2) * ulp(y^(1/2)),
63 and the total error is bounded by ulp(z1).
64 Note: if y^(1/2) is exactly representable, and ends with many zeroes,
65 then mpfr_can_round below will fail; however in that case we know that
66 Im(asin(1+i*y)) is away from +/-y^(1/2) wrt zero. */
67 if (inex == 0) /* enlarge im(z1) so that the inexact flag is correct */
68 {
69 if (mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op)))
70 mpfr_nextbelow (mpc_imagref (z1));
71 else
72 mpfr_nextabove (mpc_imagref (z1));
73 return 1;
74 }
75 p = mpfr_get_prec (mpc_imagref (z1));
76 if (!mpfr_can_round (mpc_imagref(z1), p - 1, MPFR_RNDA, MPFR_RNDZ,
77 mpfr_get_prec (mpc_imagref(rop)) +
78 (MPC_RND_IM(rnd) == MPFR_RNDN)))
79 return 0;
80 return 1;
81}
82
83int
84mpc_asin (mpc_ptr rop, mpc_srcptr op, mpc_rnd_t rnd)
85{
86 mpfr_prec_t p, p_re, p_im;
87 mpfr_rnd_t rnd_re, rnd_im;
88 mpc_t z1;
89 int inex, loop = 0;
90
91 /* special values */
92 if (mpfr_nan_p (mpc_realref (op)) || mpfr_nan_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
93 {
94 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_realref (op)) || mpfr_inf_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
95 {
96 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_realref (rop));
97 mpfr_set_inf (mpc_imagref (rop), mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op)) ? -1 : +1);
98 }
99 else if (mpfr_zero_p (mpc_realref (op)))
100 {
101 mpfr_set (mpc_realref (rop), mpc_realref (op), MPFR_RNDN);
102 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_imagref (rop));
103 }
104 else
105 {
106 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_realref (rop));
107 mpfr_set_nan (mpc_imagref (rop));
108 }
109
110 return 0;
111 }
112
113 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_realref (op)) || mpfr_inf_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
114 {
115 int inex_re;
116 if (mpfr_inf_p (mpc_realref (op)))
117 {
118 int inf_im = mpfr_inf_p (mpc_imagref (op));
119
120 inex_re = set_pi_over_2 (mpc_realref (rop),
121 (mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op)) ? -1 : 1), MPC_RND_RE (rnd));
122 mpfr_set_inf (mpc_imagref (rop), (mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op)) ? -1 : 1));
123
124 if (inf_im)
125 mpfr_div_2ui (mpc_realref (rop), mpc_realref (rop), 1, MPFR_RNDN);
126 }
127 else
128 {
129 mpfr_set_zero (mpc_realref (rop), (mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op)) ? -1 : 1));
130 inex_re = 0;
131 mpfr_set_inf (mpc_imagref (rop), (mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op)) ? -1 : 1));
132 }
133
134 return MPC_INEX (inex_re, 0);
135 }
136
137 /* pure real argument */
138 if (mpfr_zero_p (mpc_imagref (op)))
139 {
140 int inex_re;
141 int inex_im;
142 int s_im;
143 s_im = mpfr_signbit (mpc_imagref (op));
144
145 if (mpfr_cmp_ui (mpc_realref (op), 1) > 0)
146 {
147 if (s_im)
148 inex_im = -mpfr_acosh (mpc_imagref (rop), mpc_realref (op),
149 INV_RND (MPC_RND_IM (rnd)));
150 else
151 inex_im = mpfr_acosh (mpc_imagref (rop), mpc_realref (op),
152 MPC_RND_IM (rnd));
153 inex_re = set_pi_over_2 (mpc_realref (rop),
154 (mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op)) ? -1 : 1), MPC_RND_RE (rnd));
155 if (s_im)
156 mpc_conj (rop, rop, MPC_RNDNN);
157 }
158 else if (mpfr_cmp_si (mpc_realref (op), -1) < 0)
159 {
160 mpfr_t minus_op_re;
161 minus_op_re[0] = mpc_realref (op)[0];
162 MPFR_CHANGE_SIGN (minus_op_re);
163
164 if (s_im)
165 inex_im = -mpfr_acosh (mpc_imagref (rop), minus_op_re,
166 INV_RND (MPC_RND_IM (rnd)));
167 else
168 inex_im = mpfr_acosh (mpc_imagref (rop), minus_op_re,
169 MPC_RND_IM (rnd));
170 inex_re = set_pi_over_2 (mpc_realref (rop),
171 (mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op)) ? -1 : 1), MPC_RND_RE (rnd));
172 if (s_im)
173 mpc_conj (rop, rop, MPC_RNDNN);
174 }
175 else
176 {
177 inex_im = mpfr_set_ui (mpc_imagref (rop), 0, MPC_RND_IM (rnd));
178 if (s_im)
179 mpfr_neg (mpc_imagref (rop), mpc_imagref (rop), MPFR_RNDN);
180 inex_re = mpfr_asin (mpc_realref (rop), mpc_realref (op), MPC_RND_RE (rnd));
181 }
182
183 return MPC_INEX (inex_re, inex_im);
184 }
185
186 /* pure imaginary argument */
187 if (mpfr_zero_p (mpc_realref (op)))
188 {
189 int inex_im;
190 int s;
191 s = mpfr_signbit (mpc_realref (op));
192 mpfr_set_ui (mpc_realref (rop), 0, MPFR_RNDN);
193 if (s)
194 mpfr_neg (mpc_realref (rop), mpc_realref (rop), MPFR_RNDN);
195 inex_im = mpfr_asinh (mpc_imagref (rop), mpc_imagref (op), MPC_RND_IM (rnd));
196
197 return MPC_INEX (0, inex_im);
198 }
199
200 /* regular complex: asin(z) = -i*log(i*z+sqrt(1-z^2)) */
201 p_re = mpfr_get_prec (mpc_realref(rop));
202 p_im = mpfr_get_prec (mpc_imagref(rop));
203 rnd_re = MPC_RND_RE(rnd);
204 rnd_im = MPC_RND_IM(rnd);
205 p = p_re >= p_im ? p_re : p_im;
206 mpc_init2 (z1, p);
207 while (1)
208 {
209 mpfr_exp_t ex, ey, err;
210
211 loop ++;
212 p += (loop <= 2) ? mpc_ceil_log2 (p) + 3 : p / 2;
213 mpfr_set_prec (mpc_realref(z1), p);
214 mpfr_set_prec (mpc_imagref(z1), p);
215
216 /* try special code for 1+i*y with tiny y */
217 if (loop == 1 && mpc_asin_special (rop, op, rnd, z1))
218 break;
219
220 /* z1 <- z^2 */
221 mpc_sqr (z1, op, MPC_RNDNN);
222 /* err(x) <= 1/2 ulp(x), err(y) <= 1/2 ulp(y) */
223 /* z1 <- 1-z1 */
224 ex = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1));
225 mpfr_ui_sub (mpc_realref(z1), 1, mpc_realref(z1), MPFR_RNDN);
226 mpfr_neg (mpc_imagref(z1), mpc_imagref(z1), MPFR_RNDN);
227 ex = ex - mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1));
228 ex = (ex <= 0) ? 0 : ex;
229 /* err(x) <= 2^ex * ulp(x) */
230 ex = ex + mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) - p;
231 /* err(x) <= 2^ex */
232 ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1)) - p - 1;
233 /* err(y) <= 2^ey */
234 ex = (ex >= ey) ? ex : ey; /* err(x), err(y) <= 2^ex, i.e., the norm
235 of the error is bounded by |h|<=2^(ex+1/2) */
236 /* z1 <- sqrt(z1): if z1 = z + h, then sqrt(z1) = sqrt(z) + h/2/sqrt(t) */
237 ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) >= mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1))
238 ? mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) : mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1));
239 /* we have |z1| >= 2^(ey-1) thus 1/|z1| <= 2^(1-ey) */
240 mpc_sqrt (z1, z1, MPC_RNDNN);
241 ex = (2 * ex + 1) - 2 - (ey - 1); /* |h^2/4/|t| <= 2^ex */
242 ex = (ex + 1) / 2; /* ceil(ex/2) */
243 /* express ex in terms of ulp(z1) */
244 ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) <= mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1))
245 ? mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) : mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1));
246 ex = ex - ey + p;
247 /* take into account the rounding error in the mpc_sqrt call */
248 err = (ex <= 0) ? 1 : ex + 1;
249 /* err(x) <= 2^err * ulp(x), err(y) <= 2^err * ulp(y) */
250 /* z1 <- i*z + z1 */
251 ex = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1));
252 ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1));
253 mpfr_sub (mpc_realref(z1), mpc_realref(z1), mpc_imagref(op), MPFR_RNDN);
254 mpfr_add (mpc_imagref(z1), mpc_imagref(z1), mpc_realref(op), MPFR_RNDN);
255 if (mpfr_cmp_ui (mpc_realref(z1), 0) == 0 || mpfr_cmp_ui (mpc_imagref(z1), 0) == 0)
256 continue;
257 ex -= mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)); /* cancellation in x */
258 ey -= mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1)); /* cancellation in y */
259 ex = (ex >= ey) ? ex : ey; /* maximum cancellation */
260 err += ex;
261 err = (err <= 0) ? 1 : err + 1; /* rounding error in sub/add */
262 /* z1 <- log(z1): if z1 = z + h, then log(z1) = log(z) + h/t with
263 |t| >= min(|z1|,|z|) */
264 ex = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1));
265 ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1));
266 ex = (ex >= ey) ? ex : ey;
267 err += ex - p; /* revert to absolute error <= 2^err */
268 mpc_log (z1, z1, MPFR_RNDN);
269 err -= ex - 1; /* 1/|t| <= 1/|z| <= 2^(1-ex) */
270 /* express err in terms of ulp(z1) */
271 ey = mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) <= mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1))
272 ? mpfr_get_exp (mpc_realref(z1)) : mpfr_get_exp (mpc_imagref(z1));
273 err = err - ey + p;
274 /* take into account the rounding error in the mpc_log call */
275 err = (err <= 0) ? 1 : err + 1;
276 /* z1 <- -i*z1 */
277 mpfr_swap (mpc_realref(z1), mpc_imagref(z1));
278 mpfr_neg (mpc_imagref(z1), mpc_imagref(z1), MPFR_RNDN);
279 if (mpfr_can_round (mpc_realref(z1), p - err, MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
280 p_re + (rnd_re == MPFR_RNDN)) &&
281 mpfr_can_round (mpc_imagref(z1), p - err, MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
282 p_im + (rnd_im == MPFR_RNDN)))
283 break;
284 }
285
286 inex = mpc_set (rop, z1, rnd);
287 mpc_clear (z1);
288
289 return inex;
290}
